24:53.582 --> 24:55.876
<i>Hey, no. Don't do that. Don't put--</i>

24:56.293 --> 24:57.336
<i>Get it out of my--!</i>

25:01.257 --> 25:03.009
<i>Where are we going now?</i>

25:03.175 --> 25:04.552
<i>Hey, don't drop me.</i>

25:08.639 --> 25:10.433
<i>Very nice.</i>

25:14.103 --> 25:15.396
Hi.

25:18.232 --> 25:21.235
<i>Lady, I don't know about you,
but I'm beat.</i>

25:22.778 --> 25:25.781
So you're the one
that's been kicking me.

25:26.949 --> 25:29.577
<i>You were the one that ate
all that spicy food.</i>

25:32.288 --> 25:35.291
<i>This has to be the weirdest thing
that ever happened to me.</i>

25:35.499 --> 25:37.126
<i>Well, so far.</i>

25:41.338 --> 25:42.423
<i>I don't get it.</i>

25:42.673 --> 25:45.301
<i>I just don't get it, and I don't like it.</i>

25:45.509 --> 25:47.303
<i>Where did I go wrong?</i>

25:47.470 --> 25:50.389
<i>Where the hell are my thumbs?</i>

25:50.556 --> 25:53.059
<i>I want to suck my thumbs!</i>

25:53.225 --> 25:55.144
<i>I gotta get my own place.</i>

25:55.311 --> 25:58.856
<i>I did not think I'd be
reincarnated this quickly.</i>

25:59.106 --> 26:01.067
<i>What a surprise!</i>

26:01.525 --> 26:02.526
<i>Boy.</i>

26:02.693 --> 26:04.904
<i>Who stole my sucking thing!</i>

26:05.112 --> 26:07.656
<i>I need my sucking thing!</i>

26:08.032 --> 26:10.993
<i>Just remember, I hate childhood.</i>

26:20.127 --> 26:22.838
Look at all those daddies
down there...

26:23.047 --> 26:26.801
...making goofball faces
and taking pictures of their babies.

26:30.429 --> 26:33.057
Well, you won't find your father here.

26:33.224 --> 26:35.768
I really messed things up for you.

26:37.311 --> 26:40.147
Don't be upset
because I'm gonna find you a daddy.

26:40.398 --> 26:42.441
This time I'll be smart about it.

26:42.692 --> 26:46.445
I won't go for some handsome guy
just because I'm in love with him.

26:46.696 --> 26:48.531
You're all that matters to me.

26:48.781 --> 26:53.536
And I'm gonna go out there, and I'm
gonna get you the best daddy there is.

26:58.582 --> 27:02.378
<i>Out, down, in, out.</i>

27:03.170 --> 27:04.588
<i>Well, I got that.</i>

27:04.839 --> 27:06.966
What you got there, little face?

27:07.383 --> 27:09.135
A hand? Did you find a hand?

27:10.052 --> 27:11.804
<i>Yeah, I got two of them.</i>

27:20.229 --> 27:22.064
Oh, my God!

27:24.066 --> 27:26.068
Oh, God....

27:30.197 --> 27:33.993
"On the third or fourth postpartum day,
your breasts may swell slightly."

27:34.160 --> 27:37.872
"Slightly"?
I look like a Russ Meyer movie.

27:46.213 --> 27:48.049
Workman.

27:49.383 --> 27:50.676
Oh, no.

27:51.135 --> 27:52.219
Sorry.

27:52.428 --> 27:53.929
Real nice.

27:56.640 --> 27:59.268
-You got your figure back.
-This isn't my figure.

27:59.518 --> 28:01.187
You got Dolly Parton's figure back.

28:01.437 --> 28:04.023
Sorry I hit you and yelled at you
the other day.

28:04.273 --> 28:08.110
I was in a lot of pain.
I know I still owe you that cab fare.

28:08.652 --> 28:11.530
But somebody stole my purse
at the hospital.

28:11.781 --> 28:14.367
How you doing, pal?
How do you like New York?

28:14.617 --> 28:16.452
<i>It's my kind of town.</i>

28:16.702 --> 28:19.830
This is a crummy tip,
but I'll get back to you later.

28:20.247 --> 28:23.751
Wait a minute.
How did you know where I lived?

28:26.712 --> 28:27.963
You left it in the cab.

28:29.715 --> 28:31.092
Thanks.

28:31.759 --> 28:33.803
-You never look through it.
-Why do you say that?

28:34.053 --> 28:36.389
You're still carrying your diaphragm.

28:42.853 --> 28:45.731
Don't smoke that around my baby!

28:45.981 --> 28:48.859
There's a 62 percent higher rate
of getting cancer...

28:49.110 --> 28:51.320
...for non-smokers who live
with smokers.

28:51.529 --> 28:54.240
So you don't want me to move in yet?

28:57.076 --> 28:59.203
I don't know. What do you think?

28:59.412 --> 29:01.831
Did the drugs have any effect on him?

29:02.039 --> 29:04.041
How did you know I had drugs?

29:04.834 --> 29:06.877
I don't. I didn't. It's just....

29:07.128 --> 29:09.714
You can tell in his eyes.
He looks stoned.

29:09.922 --> 29:11.924
He doesn't look stoned!

29:12.842 --> 29:14.719
He looks perfect.

29:14.927 --> 29:17.263
You don't look so hot yourself.

29:17.722 --> 29:21.892
Squeeze a thing as big as a watermelon
out of an opening as big as a lemon...

29:22.143 --> 29:23.811
...and see how hot you look.

29:25.021 --> 29:27.898
I should call my mother more often.
Get it?

29:28.357 --> 29:29.525
You want a sub?

29:29.775 --> 29:32.862
No. Will you just watch him
while I change clothes?

29:33.487 --> 29:37.199
Don't take him out of his chair,
and don't touch him a whole lot.

29:40.745 --> 29:43.247
-How are you, Mikey? I'm James.
<i>-Hey, James.</i>

29:43.414 --> 29:44.957
-Good to meet you.
<i>-Can I suck on that?</i>

29:45.416 --> 29:47.001
Sweet.

29:49.628 --> 29:51.130
So how long you been here?

29:51.338 --> 29:53.007
About five years.

29:53.341 --> 29:55.134
In the same apartment?

29:55.384 --> 29:56.510
Yes.

29:56.677 --> 29:58.054
Were you born in New York?

29:58.220 --> 30:02.016
Yeah. What are you,
with the Census Bureau or something?

30:03.893 --> 30:05.478
Do you like the outside world?

30:06.520 --> 30:08.689
You spend nine months
trying to get out...

30:08.898 --> 30:11.317
...and the rest of your life
trying to get back in.

30:11.484 --> 30:13.235
<i>Yeah, tell me about it.</i>

30:13.486 --> 30:17.281
This? This here is your first lesson
in coffee.

30:17.448 --> 30:19.617
With nothing in it, it's black coffee.

30:19.784 --> 30:21.243
Can you say "black coffee"?

30:21.994 --> 30:26.707
Then there's coffee regular.
That means two sugars and milk.

30:27.083 --> 30:29.835
Which they forgot.
So can I borrow some of yours?

30:33.547 --> 30:35.758
Coffee regular. I love it.

30:35.925 --> 30:37.551
That's breast milk.

30:41.180 --> 30:42.431
Why didn't you tell me?

30:42.640 --> 30:44.558
<i>Hey, man, you're on your own.</i>

30:45.476 --> 30:48.479
I'll see you guys later, okay?

30:48.729 --> 30:52.900
I'm gonna take my sub and my breast
milk and I'm gonna get out of here.

30:53.109 --> 30:54.610
<i>Be cool, James.</i>

30:54.819 --> 30:58.698
<i>Okay, fellas, I got something
cold and wet in my shorts down here.</i>

30:58.989 --> 31:01.325
<i>Can you get somebody for me? Guys?</i>

31:01.701 --> 31:02.993
<i>Listen, fellas?</i>

31:04.370 --> 31:05.746
<i>You guys are no help.</i>

31:06.038 --> 31:08.916
<i>I'm cold and wet
and there's nothing I can do.</i>

31:11.252 --> 31:14.547
It's okay, Mikey. Mommy's here.

31:15.297 --> 31:18.634
<i>Very nice.
That mommy person's here again.</i>

31:18.843 --> 31:21.470
<i>She's okay. I like her.</i>

31:21.679 --> 31:23.723
That's a good boy.

31:24.181 --> 31:28.602
<i>Let me get this straight: I start
crying and she comes in with a bottle.</i>

31:28.769 --> 31:31.897
<i>Crying.
I can definitely handle crying.</i>

32:14.857 --> 32:16.192
Taxi!

32:44.428 --> 32:47.139
"Due to changing hormones,
over 80 percent of all women...

32:47.348 --> 32:49.767
...experience postpartum depression."

32:50.851 --> 32:52.061
I'm not gonna.

32:55.481 --> 32:59.318
<i>Like many parents, I can't always be
home for a loved one's birthday.</i>

33:01.612 --> 33:05.533
<i>Help, help! Somebody burp me
before I blow up.</i>

33:07.785 --> 33:08.828
<i>Thank you.</i>

33:09.078 --> 33:12.707
That's it. You have
some exotic baby disease...

33:12.915 --> 33:15.918
...and I look like the lead
in <i>Night of the Living Dead.</i>

33:16.168 --> 33:20.881
And your father deserted us so that
he could pork his interior decorator.

33:21.507 --> 33:25.761
I think you can safely say
that it can't get any worse.

33:25.970 --> 33:27.304
Hello!

33:27.555 --> 33:29.223
I was wrong.

33:30.891 --> 33:33.769
Where's my grandson?

33:36.188 --> 33:38.190
There he is.

33:41.110 --> 33:44.655
Hello, Mikey. Do you know who I am?

33:44.905 --> 33:46.949
<i>No, actually, I don't.</i>

33:47.199 --> 33:48.951
I'm your grandma!

33:49.160 --> 33:51.954
<i>Okay, lady. If you say so,
you're my grandma.</i>

33:52.204 --> 33:55.624
-Yes, I am.
<i>-So, what do you want from me?</i>

33:59.587 --> 34:02.089
Who's got a wet tushy?

34:02.923 --> 34:03.966
<i>I give up.</i>

34:04.550 --> 34:05.885
Tushy, tushy, tushy....

34:08.763 --> 34:13.184
<i>After a new diaper, I really like some
of that white stuff on me. All right?</i>

34:13.392 --> 34:15.269
<i>Have you got it? There it is.</i>

34:15.603 --> 34:18.439
<i>Put some on me. Come on.</i>

34:19.648 --> 34:21.942
<i>Just give it to me and I'll put it on.</i>

34:22.151 --> 34:25.988
<i>Let me get my hands on it
and I'll put it on.</i>

34:27.615 --> 34:30.743
<i>-There we go.
</i>-You put way too much powder on him.

34:30.951 --> 34:35.623
Why don't you get out of this house?
I'm gonna give Mikey a little bath.

34:35.873 --> 34:37.583
We're gonna have a "bubba."

34:37.792 --> 34:39.126
<i>A what?</i>

34:42.838 --> 34:44.799
<i>Oh, yeah, she's gone.</i>

34:52.723 --> 34:56.435
If love didn't exist, what guy
would you get to be your kid's father?

34:56.686 --> 35:00.189
Someone with a small mouth
and good hair, broad shoulders--

35:00.439 --> 35:04.944
No, what kind of man do you want to
stick around and help raise your child?

35:05.152 --> 35:06.821
Are there men who do that?

35:07.321 --> 35:10.032
I know what I'm looking for.

35:10.324 --> 35:14.286
A guy who's not married,
not into drugs, not an alcoholic...

35:14.495 --> 35:17.248
...not a deadbeat, but who doesn't
work 20 hours a day.

35:17.498 --> 35:20.209
-And cute.
-Cute is not a consideration.

35:20.501 --> 35:21.502
Come on!

35:21.711 --> 35:23.963
Cute is of absolutely no importance.

35:25.297 --> 35:27.508
<i>You're my first date
since my baby was born.</i>

35:27.675 --> 35:30.553
This looks delicious.
I've heard great things--

35:30.720 --> 35:32.304
Helen, or whatever....

35:32.555 --> 35:36.267
What is this?
I asked for well-done. This is raw.

35:36.517 --> 35:40.438
I asked for no dressing!
This is covered with slop.

35:40.855 --> 35:42.273
Are you deaf?

35:42.481 --> 35:46.694
Who do you have to kill to get those
rolls I see on the other tables?

35:46.944 --> 35:48.696
A "C" in algebra?

35:48.946 --> 35:54.076
How many times did we go over and over
and over and over those logarithms?

35:54.410 --> 35:56.662
What are you, some kind of an idiot?

35:56.912 --> 36:00.291
I've never dated anyone
from the health club before.

36:00.499 --> 36:04.295
But I said, "What the hell?
You gotta take a chance sometime."

36:04.503 --> 36:06.088
I'm not so sure about that.

36:06.380 --> 36:11.052
Excuse me. This fork is dirty,
this plate looks spotty...

36:11.344 --> 36:14.722
...and there's something
floating around in this water.

36:15.431 --> 36:17.850
Have you checked your water?

36:18.059 --> 36:19.894
Mikey, what is this mess?

36:20.603 --> 36:24.190
Why are white socks in the same row
with coloured socks?

36:24.482 --> 36:28.569
And what are school shirts doing
mixed up with after-school shirts?

36:29.070 --> 36:32.156
You're not going anywhere till
this is straightened up.

36:39.830 --> 36:42.416
-Hi.
-Hey.

36:42.583 --> 36:45.628
-Somebody call for a cab?
-Yeah. Small world.

36:46.796 --> 36:49.090
More mail for Vincent Ubriacco.

36:50.049 --> 36:52.635
-I don't even know him.
-Let me have them.

36:52.927 --> 36:56.931
All you do is put them up here
and the postman will take care of them.

36:57.431 --> 36:58.474
Good to see you.

36:58.683 --> 37:00.518
It's good seeing you too.

37:00.726 --> 37:01.936
See you.

37:07.775 --> 37:10.486
You son of a bitch!
You're stealing my mail!

37:10.736 --> 37:12.863
-I am not.
-What's in your pocket?

37:13.072 --> 37:15.700
-They're mine.
-You got it out of my mailbox!

37:15.950 --> 37:19.245
No, look, I sent them here.
Can I explain?

37:19.453 --> 37:21.205
Do it fast, or I'll call the police.

37:21.455 --> 37:25.543
My grandfather, Vincent, has been
kicked out of an old-age home.

37:25.751 --> 37:27.837
I found a place for him in Manhattan.

37:28.045 --> 37:31.090
But I'm not a resident.
I live in Englewood. So....

37:31.298 --> 37:33.592
You used my address
to set up residency.

37:33.759 --> 37:35.136
Yeah. Well, that's-- Yeah.

37:35.553 --> 37:37.847
-I could have you arrested for this.
-For what?

37:38.097 --> 37:40.933
Screwing with the mail is
a federal offence.

37:41.142 --> 37:44.270
Stealing mail is a federal offence,
not screwing with it.

37:44.979 --> 37:46.939
-Can I get the other letters?
-No.

37:47.148 --> 37:49.316
-Why not?
-I don't want to get involved.

37:49.567 --> 37:52.778
I go out of my way
to bring back your purse...

37:52.987 --> 37:55.781
...so you don't have to cancel
your credit cards.

37:55.990 --> 37:57.700
Thank you very much.

37:58.242 --> 38:01.162
This is illegal.
And I don't want to get caught.

38:01.412 --> 38:04.874
You're not gonna get caught.
I'll do something for you.

38:05.124 --> 38:06.459
Like what?

38:06.667 --> 38:08.210
I'll babysit.

38:09.336 --> 38:12.631
Come on. You don't know how
to take care of a baby.

38:12.882 --> 38:15.676
I do. I practically brought up
my sister's kids.

38:15.926 --> 38:17.803
I know a lot about babies.

38:18.137 --> 38:20.598
All right, then. Friday nights.

38:21.015 --> 38:24.268
No, I can't do it. Friday's out.

38:24.602 --> 38:26.520
Then forget the whole deal.

38:26.896 --> 38:28.814
Friday's okay, but that's it.

38:29.065 --> 38:30.608
And during my aerobics classes.

38:30.858 --> 38:32.485
I said that's it.

38:32.693 --> 38:34.236
One aerobics class.

38:34.487 --> 38:35.780
Saturday.

38:36.030 --> 38:37.865
-Can't do it.
-Why?

38:38.032 --> 38:41.202
-I teach.
-What to you teach? Taxi Driver's Ed?

38:42.703 --> 38:43.829
That's not funny.

38:44.038 --> 38:46.040
All right, here's the deal.

38:46.290 --> 38:49.794
Friday nights, two aerobics classes,
and no chicks over.

38:50.294 --> 38:51.837
<i>No, don't give in.</i>

38:52.546 --> 38:56.634
You're pushing it.
All right, it's a deal.

38:56.884 --> 38:58.260
<i>Sucker.</i>

38:58.511 --> 38:59.970
Good.

39:00.137 --> 39:02.682
<i>-No milk.
</i>-Don't force-feed him like that.

39:02.890 --> 39:05.351
-I'm not. He needs a nap.
<i>-No naps.</i>

39:05.601 --> 39:07.144
It doesn't look like it.

39:07.353 --> 39:09.730
A baby doesn't know what he needs.

39:09.939 --> 39:11.565
He knows he's not tired.
You tired?

39:11.941 --> 39:14.568
<i>No, man, I'm not tired at all.</i>

39:15.778 --> 39:19.407
If he doesn't take a nap,
then he will wake up...

39:19.615 --> 39:22.201
...and want to eat
when it's time to sleep.

39:22.410 --> 39:24.495
<i>Yeah, you need a nap.</i>

39:24.704 --> 39:26.247
-Who says?
-All those doctors.

39:26.497 --> 39:30.584
All those doctors. They write a book,
they want to sell a book.

39:31.085 --> 39:33.254
Dr Spock doesn't just want to
sell a book.

39:33.629 --> 39:36.841
Dr Spock loves us.
During the Vietnam War, Dr Spock....

39:37.133 --> 39:38.342
<i>You're funny.</i>

39:38.592 --> 39:41.762
I'm sorry I said anything
about Dr Spock, okay?

39:42.972 --> 39:45.558
I can't believe she's so upset
about a Vulcan.

39:45.808 --> 39:47.768
Big ears, no emotions, right?

39:48.602 --> 39:49.645
Got the letters?

39:50.021 --> 39:51.689
They're in the hallway.

40:07.955 --> 40:09.623
Mommy's asleep.

40:10.332 --> 40:11.792
Watch this.

40:39.320 --> 40:44.158
Mikey, what do you say you and me
take a ride so your mother can sleep?

40:44.450 --> 40:46.369
