01:00:50.072 --> 01:00:53.617
-Tell him not to touch my teeth.
-I will. Don't touch his teeth.

01:00:57.455 --> 01:00:59.040
Welcome, Gramps.

01:01:01.375 --> 01:01:05.046
-We stopping for a bite to eat?
-No, this is your new place.

01:01:07.256 --> 01:01:10.968
-They got good shrimp here.
-Yeah, but try the lobster.

01:01:11.218 --> 01:01:14.472
-This is it. Enjoy your stay.
-Thank you.

01:01:14.680 --> 01:01:17.850
Grandpa, this is great!
This is great. Look at this.

01:01:18.059 --> 01:01:19.727
You got a terrific view.

01:01:19.935 --> 01:01:23.606
You got no roommate to bug you,
colour television. Look at that.

01:01:23.814 --> 01:01:25.358
Can I talk to you?

01:01:26.734 --> 01:01:30.488
He loves sugar. This is enough candy
to last him a month.

01:01:30.696 --> 01:01:32.990
Give him one candy bar a day.
That's it.

01:01:33.199 --> 01:01:35.493
Don't let him find it
or he'll eat it all.

01:01:35.701 --> 01:01:36.994
No problem.

01:01:38.954 --> 01:01:40.581
Smells good, huh?

01:01:41.457 --> 01:01:43.959
Grandpa, it smells good.

01:01:44.335 --> 01:01:46.337
I'd like to see you eat it.

01:01:47.963 --> 01:01:49.298
Watch this.

01:01:53.302 --> 01:01:55.012
Let me try that.

01:01:59.517 --> 01:02:01.143
What do you want?

01:02:01.310 --> 01:02:03.354
Mollie helped us get into this place.

01:02:03.521 --> 01:02:08.025
Women have thousands more nerves
in their sexual organs than men.

01:02:10.152 --> 01:02:14.073
-I bet the kid's not even yours.
-Now, that's it. Be nice.

01:02:17.535 --> 01:02:20.371
<i>Oh, my God.
This guy's worse at this than I am.</i>

01:02:20.579 --> 01:02:22.581
<i>Here, let me give you a hand.</i>

01:02:22.790 --> 01:02:26.001
<i>Open up. Come on, taste it.</i>

01:02:26.210 --> 01:02:28.045
<i>Open wide. There we go!</i>

01:02:32.466 --> 01:02:34.927
-Thanks for helping me.
-You're welcome.

01:02:35.136 --> 01:02:36.220
Want to go flying?

01:02:36.470 --> 01:02:39.056
No, that would be
too expensive for you.

01:02:39.265 --> 01:02:42.059
If I say it's a maintenance flight,
it's free.

01:02:42.268 --> 01:02:44.812
You get everything for free.

01:02:45.187 --> 01:02:49.775
Free long-distance phone calls,
free lunches. You're a scam artist.

01:02:49.984 --> 01:02:52.069
I got the town wired, don't I?

01:02:52.319 --> 01:02:56.198
Think about it. If we were poor,
we could still live like kings.

01:02:56.782 --> 01:02:58.034
Fly with me.

01:02:58.242 --> 01:03:00.369
I'm not that kind of person.

01:03:00.578 --> 01:03:02.663
-Come on.
-It's just not my deal.

01:03:02.913 --> 01:03:05.416
-You scared?
-No, I'm not scared.

01:03:06.292 --> 01:03:07.543
<i>Where are the parachutes?</i>

01:03:08.127 --> 01:03:11.047
Parachutes?
No, there are no parachutes.

01:03:11.297 --> 01:03:13.007
No parachutes?

01:03:13.507 --> 01:03:17.053
Didn't you ever see <i>Sweet Dreams?
The Buddy Holly Story? La Bamba?</i>

01:03:17.261 --> 01:03:21.849
There's one big difference here.
They were rock legends. You're not.

01:03:24.393 --> 01:03:26.687
Are you sure
your wing's not smoking?

01:03:26.937 --> 01:03:28.147
Oh, my God!

01:03:28.647 --> 01:03:31.067
Just kidding.
It was a joke to relax you.

01:03:31.317 --> 01:03:34.820
I'm so nervous.
I feel so out of control.

01:03:35.029 --> 01:03:36.530
This is what we'll do.

01:03:36.739 --> 01:03:38.866
I'm gonna give you your first lesson.

01:03:39.075 --> 01:03:41.702
-Put your hand on my stick.
-I don't want to.

01:03:41.911 --> 01:03:43.996
-Just put it on my stick.
-No.

01:03:44.205 --> 01:03:47.708
This is not a sexual thing.
Put it on my stick.

01:03:48.167 --> 01:03:50.711
That feels good, baby.
I'm just teasing.

01:03:51.462 --> 01:03:54.965
Get familiar with the stick.
You'll be fine.

01:03:55.132 --> 01:03:56.634
-You're flying.
-I'm not.

01:03:56.842 --> 01:03:58.928
-I'm flying!
-That's it.

01:03:59.136 --> 01:04:00.179
I'm flying.

01:04:00.471 --> 01:04:03.683
-I'm doing a good job. This is easy!
-Yes, you are.

01:04:04.183 --> 01:04:06.477
Oh, God, what a good sensation.

01:04:06.644 --> 01:04:08.813
It's like great sex, isn't it?

01:04:09.063 --> 01:04:11.440
I personally wouldn't remember.

01:04:12.817 --> 01:04:14.443
He's pretty tired, huh?

01:04:14.652 --> 01:04:16.904
Yeah, he's had a busy day.

01:04:21.242 --> 01:04:22.952
-Want to watch a movie?
-Want a drink?

01:04:23.619 --> 01:04:25.871
-If there's a good movie on.
-Yeah, a beer--

01:05:22.845 --> 01:05:25.056
Stop it, stop it!

01:05:25.264 --> 01:05:26.515
Stop yelling!

01:05:26.724 --> 01:05:30.353
Your father will give you
something to yell about!

01:05:30.561 --> 01:05:32.688
Hey, knock it off!

01:05:34.482 --> 01:05:38.611
Princess, you're making
my mouth water.

01:05:39.779 --> 01:05:41.447
I'm hungry.

01:05:41.864 --> 01:05:44.742
Hold your horses,
or I'll knock you to kingdom come.

01:05:44.950 --> 01:05:48.621
Is that any way for a royal family
to behave? I don't think so.

01:05:48.829 --> 01:05:52.833
Look what I found in that dumpster
behind the supermarket.

01:05:53.042 --> 01:05:54.960
A perfectly good head of lettuce.

01:05:55.169 --> 01:05:58.089
All you got to do
is peel off the outside.

01:05:58.297 --> 01:06:00.007
Who wants a surprise?

01:06:00.216 --> 01:06:02.134
-I do. I do.
-I do. I do.

01:06:02.301 --> 01:06:05.304
Could be lunch meat,
could be peaches. Who knows?

01:06:05.513 --> 01:06:09.392
Even though it's free don't mean
it's no good. Right, princess?

01:06:09.809 --> 01:06:11.310
You're right, honey.

01:06:11.477 --> 01:06:13.270
I told you we'd live like kings.

01:06:13.437 --> 01:06:14.563
You sure did.

01:06:19.527 --> 01:06:20.695
Again, again.

01:06:22.071 --> 01:06:23.948
Do it again!

01:06:26.826 --> 01:06:28.494
Again! Again!

01:06:29.203 --> 01:06:30.371
Wait a minute!

01:06:32.289 --> 01:06:34.291
I'm sorry. I really am.

01:06:34.458 --> 01:06:36.669
-I really do want this.
-I do too.

01:06:36.836 --> 01:06:38.921
-It's Mikey.
-He's asleep.

01:06:39.130 --> 01:06:41.424
I have to be clear
in the choices I make.

01:06:41.674 --> 01:06:44.176
I can't get all swept up
in sex and emotion.

01:06:44.427 --> 01:06:46.387
That's how I got in trouble.

01:06:46.595 --> 01:06:49.432
I can't be like a teenager
who falls for someone...

01:06:49.640 --> 01:06:51.267
...then realises it was a mistake.

01:06:51.475 --> 01:06:53.352
The one who gets hurt is Mikey.

01:06:53.561 --> 01:06:55.771
I'm crazy about Mikey and about you.

01:06:55.980 --> 01:06:59.316
Please don't hate me.
I know I was leading you on.

01:06:59.525 --> 01:07:03.320
You're such a good kisser,
and I haven't had sex in a long time.

01:07:04.739 --> 01:07:06.949
Goodbye. Please.

01:07:07.783 --> 01:07:09.160
Goodbye.

01:07:10.244 --> 01:07:12.455
-Mollie, can I talk to you?
-Yeah?

01:07:13.039 --> 01:07:14.874
Could you hold, please?

01:07:15.708 --> 01:07:18.544
Let me ask you a question,
between you and me.

01:07:19.045 --> 01:07:21.088
What's with you and Chubby Charles?

01:07:21.297 --> 01:07:23.966
-What do you mean?
-What do I mean?

01:07:24.342 --> 01:07:26.469
Perlman's doing the bank records.

01:07:26.677 --> 01:07:28.554
Rubenstein did
the corporate quarterlies.

01:07:28.804 --> 01:07:31.724
And now there's an extension
on Albert's return.

01:07:31.891 --> 01:07:33.726
What's with you and Chubby Charles?

01:07:33.893 --> 01:07:36.228
I made up my work
from my maternity leave.

01:07:36.437 --> 01:07:39.857
I traded Rubenstein two accounts
for the Chubby Charles' account...

01:07:40.066 --> 01:07:43.611
...because I can't do it anymore.
It's personal.

01:07:44.779 --> 01:07:48.366
I don't understand.
We're accountants. We're not personal.

01:07:49.241 --> 01:07:52.411
-But I don't think that you--
-You've been his accountant for years.

01:07:52.578 --> 01:07:55.831
Now when he needs you the most,
you desert him?

01:07:56.082 --> 01:07:59.543
-You don't understand--
-I want you up there tomorrow.

01:07:59.710 --> 01:08:01.045
And that's final.

01:08:02.046 --> 01:08:03.964
Don't give me that look.

01:08:04.131 --> 01:08:06.717
And you, showtime's over.
Get back to work.

01:08:10.429 --> 01:08:13.683
Mollie, you have to give me
a second chance.

01:08:13.891 --> 01:08:16.102
These past months
have been a bad dream.

01:08:16.394 --> 01:08:19.605
I felt so guilty
leaving Beth and the girls.

01:08:19.855 --> 01:08:22.525
Albert, you have been such an asshole.

01:08:22.733 --> 01:08:26.654
If we got back together,
I'd torture you for the rest of your life.

01:08:27.279 --> 01:08:29.198
That's okay, I want you to.

01:08:29.407 --> 01:08:32.451
Oh, Mollie, Mollie, Mollie....

01:08:33.619 --> 01:08:36.747
-What?
-I'll burst if I don't kiss you soon.

01:08:37.915 --> 01:08:39.083
Tough.

01:08:43.170 --> 01:08:44.463
Albert can see you now.

01:08:52.263 --> 01:08:53.973
Mollie....

01:08:54.140 --> 01:08:56.183
-How's Mickey?
-Mikey.

01:08:56.350 --> 01:08:58.853
-Is he talking yet?
-No.

01:08:59.562 --> 01:09:01.272
-Crawling?
-Yes.

01:09:01.522 --> 01:09:03.274
The first time Astrid crawled--

01:09:03.482 --> 01:09:07.486
I'm not interested in anecdotes
starring you as the good father.

01:09:07.737 --> 01:09:10.114
I've been meaning to talk to you.

01:09:10.281 --> 01:09:13.451
I'm here to do your taxes, not talk.

01:09:16.787 --> 01:09:19.749
"Bloomingdale's," "eyelash tinting,"
"body wraps," "facials--"

01:09:19.999 --> 01:09:21.959
You can't deduct this crap.

01:09:22.168 --> 01:09:25.171
Could the personal exercise instructor
be a medical expense?

01:09:25.379 --> 01:09:27.757
Did she suffer injuries
that needed therapy?

01:09:28.007 --> 01:09:30.384
-No.
-Then you can't.

01:09:30.634 --> 01:09:33.137
So what's the little woman been up to?

01:09:34.388 --> 01:09:37.683
Is Priscilla sick?
Why all these doctor bills?

01:09:37.892 --> 01:09:41.270
Her therapy. Beth's been
communicating with the dead.

01:09:41.479 --> 01:09:44.648
It was really frightening for Priscilla.

01:09:44.857 --> 01:09:47.068
We're all seeing
a psychiatrist together.

01:09:47.902 --> 01:09:50.071
I've been learning a lot.

01:09:50.988 --> 01:09:52.698
I'm happy for you.

01:09:52.948 --> 01:09:55.785
I know you've been through a lot.

01:09:56.202 --> 01:09:58.079
But you gotta believe I love you.

01:09:58.329 --> 01:10:03.084
I never wanted anything bad to happen
to you. But I realise it did.

01:10:03.334 --> 01:10:06.629
It took you $20,000
to figure that out?

01:10:07.296 --> 01:10:09.382
-Do you have a picture of Mickey?
-Mikey!

01:10:09.632 --> 01:10:12.176
I'm sorry. I'm very nervous.

01:10:12.843 --> 01:10:15.096
I think about you and Mikey every day.

01:10:15.304 --> 01:10:16.847
You'd never know it from our end.

01:10:17.056 --> 01:10:20.601
I try to call every day
and I can't do it.

01:10:20.810 --> 01:10:25.564
I'm too ashamed to say anything,
and I'm too afraid of what you'll say.

01:10:26.232 --> 01:10:27.608
I've been so confused.

01:10:40.955 --> 01:10:42.540
He has my eyes.

01:10:42.707 --> 01:10:44.166
I know he does.

01:10:44.667 --> 01:10:49.004
It's very confusing to love someone so
much who looks like someone you hate.

01:10:49.171 --> 01:10:51.465
Can I see him, Mollie? Please?

01:10:55.052 --> 01:10:58.514
All right.
I'll be home later on this evening.

01:10:59.473 --> 01:11:03.102
Next time you talk to your mom,
put in a good word for me.

01:11:03.310 --> 01:11:04.353
Want a hit?

01:11:04.562 --> 01:11:05.688
<i>Hit me.</i>

01:11:06.605 --> 01:11:07.606
<i>Again.</i>

01:11:07.773 --> 01:11:10.192
-No, no. Yeah?
<i>-Hit it again.</i>

01:11:10.401 --> 01:11:13.029
-All right.
<i>-I know what I'm doing.</i>

01:11:13.571 --> 01:11:14.822
One for me.

01:11:15.531 --> 01:11:16.782
Damn! You won again.

01:11:17.283 --> 01:11:18.409
<i>I told you I could play.</i>

01:11:18.617 --> 01:11:22.580
<i>Listen, I've been thinking
about this Daddy business.</i>

01:11:22.830 --> 01:11:26.375
<i>I want you to be my daddy.
I'll tell Mommy about it.</i>

01:11:28.878 --> 01:11:30.129
Who is it?

01:11:35.885 --> 01:11:38.387
-Is Mollie here?
-She's at aerobics class.

01:11:38.637 --> 01:11:40.056
Call in an hour.

01:11:41.349 --> 01:11:43.809
-Is Mikey here?
-Who are you?

01:11:43.976 --> 01:11:45.895
-I'm his father.
-Father?

01:11:46.062 --> 01:11:48.439
Are you the sperm donor?

01:11:48.606 --> 01:11:50.524
Sperm donor? I'm the kid's father.

01:11:50.691 --> 01:11:53.444
He has no father.
He's from artificial insemination.

01:11:53.611 --> 01:11:56.697
That's ridiculous. Mollie and I
have been going out for years.

01:11:56.906 --> 01:11:58.449
How do you think I have the key?

01:11:58.657 --> 01:12:00.534
I don't know, but we're changing it.

01:12:00.743 --> 01:12:02.745
-Hey.
-What? What?

01:12:02.953 --> 01:12:05.331
That's my kid in there. Let me by.

01:12:05.581 --> 01:12:09.502
If you're the father,
you can answer a few questions for me.

01:12:09.710 --> 01:12:11.837
-When was he born?
-July 3rd.

01:12:12.004 --> 01:12:13.381
His favourite cereal?

01:12:13.547 --> 01:12:14.840
-I don't know.
-Cheerios.

01:12:15.007 --> 01:12:16.425
His favourite stuffed animal?

01:12:17.051 --> 01:12:18.386
-Fred.
-Right.

01:12:18.594 --> 01:12:19.720
No, Barney.

01:12:19.929 --> 01:12:22.223
How many diapers does
he go through a day? Six.

01:12:22.390 --> 01:12:23.891
Who's his favourite rock star?
Michael Jackson.

01:12:24.058 --> 01:12:26.185
Shouldn't a father know these things?

01:12:26.352 --> 01:12:28.396
How much does she pay you,
$5 an hour?

01:12:28.604 --> 01:12:31.065
-Go play some video games.
-Don't give me that shit!

01:12:31.232 --> 01:12:33.067
Punk.

01:12:34.694 --> 01:12:37.530
Come on, "Dad." Let's go.

01:12:39.198 --> 01:12:40.825
<i>Go for the body!</i>

01:12:48.082 --> 01:12:50.751
Get out of here.
Come on, get out.

01:12:54.213 --> 01:12:57.383
Oh, yes. That feels good.

01:13:04.515 --> 01:13:05.891
What happened?

01:13:06.434 --> 01:13:07.977
Who's Albert?

01:13:09.186 --> 01:13:10.396
Why, was he here?

01:13:10.604 --> 01:13:11.814
Is he Mikey's father?

01:13:12.273 --> 01:13:13.441
What?

01:13:15.609 --> 01:13:19.155
You lied to me about
the artificial-insemination crap.

01:13:19.405 --> 01:13:21.574
He was married.
I couldn't tell anyone.

01:13:21.782 --> 01:13:23.200
Do you love him?

01:13:23.659 --> 01:13:24.785
Do you?

01:13:26.287 --> 01:13:28.289
-What?
-Do you love him?

01:13:28.706 --> 01:13:29.832
I don't know.

01:13:30.041 --> 01:13:32.251
I don't know who I love.

01:13:33.169 --> 01:13:37.798
And it doesn't matter. The only thing
that matters is who's best for Mikey.

01:13:38.007 --> 01:13:40.926
And Albert is
successful, responsible...

01:13:41.135 --> 01:13:43.179
...and he's good to his other kids.

01:13:45.431 --> 01:13:46.974
I don't want him seeing Mikey.

01:13:47.224 --> 01:13:50.519
Oh, no. Don't start
pulling this on me!

01:13:51.062 --> 01:13:54.357
He's his son. He has a right
to see him anytime he wants.

01:13:54.565 --> 01:13:56.192
Where has he been all year?

01:13:56.400 --> 01:13:59.570
This has nothing to do with you.
You are not his father.

01:13:59.779 --> 01:14:02.073
I'm the closest thing he's got.

01:14:02.281 --> 01:14:05.743
Oh, please. Look at you.
You're like a big kid.

01:14:06.410 --> 01:14:09.038
You think you're responsible enough
to be a father?

01:14:09.622 --> 01:14:10.873
Responsible?

01:14:11.123 --> 01:14:14.460
You call getting pregnant
by a married guy responsible?

01:14:14.627 --> 01:14:16.128
-Stop it!
-You stop.

01:14:16.295 --> 01:14:19.548
-You stop!
-You stop. I've seen you use Mikey...

01:14:19.715 --> 01:14:21.509
...to push guys away,
and now you're doing it to me.

01:14:21.676 --> 01:14:23.803
That's it! I've had it.

01:14:24.011 --> 01:14:25.721
-Get out!
-I live here!

01:14:25.888 --> 01:14:27.223
I know it!

01:14:35.481 --> 01:14:37.983
Can a person past
a certain age change?

01:14:38.192 --> 01:14:40.069
Sure. Look at Daddy.

01:14:40.277 --> 01:14:42.863
His high-density lipids
went from 230 to 185.

01:14:43.114 --> 01:14:44.865
I'm not talking about cholesterol.

01:14:45.116 --> 01:14:48.327
Can someone go through a bad phase
and then be nicer?

01:14:48.869 --> 01:14:50.705
That I don't know about.

01:14:50.913 --> 01:14:55.459
When you met Daddy at that vets' dance,
how'd you know he'd be a good father?

01:14:55.668 --> 01:14:58.879
I didn't. I liked the way
he looked in his uniform.

01:15:00.006 --> 01:15:01.966
Didn't they all look good?

01:15:02.174 --> 01:15:05.219
No, I didn't like the sailors
in their bell-bottoms.

01:15:05.428 --> 01:15:08.472
You married a man because
he looked cute in a uniform?

01:15:08.681 --> 01:15:11.726
You had no idea if he was
a mature, responsible person.

01:15:12.143 --> 01:15:15.229
If I thought like that, we wouldn't
have survived the first week.

01:15:15.396 --> 01:15:17.356
And that was some week.

01:15:17.815 --> 01:15:21.736
You're grossing me out.
Don't talk about sex and Daddy.

01:15:34.081 --> 01:15:36.125
Gerber face, high-five.

01:15:36.834 --> 01:15:38.377
Yeah.

01:15:40.713 --> 01:15:42.214
Look, Mikey....

01:15:44.091 --> 01:15:46.427
I can't come around
to see you anymore.

01:15:46.635 --> 01:15:49.680
<i>-What's the matter?
</i>-It's your mom.

01:15:50.222 --> 01:15:54.810
She has this crazy idea that I wouldn't
make a good enough father for you.

01:15:55.478 --> 01:15:56.771
Whatever that is.

01:15:56.979 --> 01:15:59.273
She wouldn't have picked
my father either.

01:15:59.482 --> 01:16:02.193
I think he did an okay job, but....

01:16:04.362 --> 01:16:06.238
Want to hear some fatherly advice?

01:16:15.081 --> 01:16:17.416
Okay, I'll write you a cheque.

01:16:18.959 --> 01:16:20.544
When I was 3...

01:16:20.795 --> 01:16:25.132
...he said, "Don't hit girls,
even if they're asking for it."

01:16:25.383 --> 01:16:27.426
<i>What'd he say about pushing them?</i>

01:16:27.927 --> 01:16:32.348
<i>Then he said, "Finish your meat.
You know how much that cost?"</i>

01:16:32.890 --> 01:16:35.518
<i>And let's see-- Oh, yeah.</i>

01:16:36.060 --> 01:16:40.189
The one that sticks out the most,
though, was probably:

01:16:41.565 --> 01:16:45.778
"If your friends jump off the Brooklyn
Bridge, does that mean you got to?"

01:16:46.028 --> 01:16:50.533
I still use that one. To this day,
I still use that piece of advice.

01:16:55.579 --> 01:16:57.748
Doesn't amount to much, does it?

01:16:58.416 --> 01:17:00.126
I think being a good father...

01:17:00.376 --> 01:17:04.380
...is keeping the mother happy
so she doesn't drive the kids crazy.

01:17:05.923 --> 01:17:09.760
<i>She called me a big kid.
She's probably right.</i>

01:17:09.969 --> 01:17:13.556
<i>You're 1 year old and probably
my best friend in the world.</i>

01:17:14.557 --> 01:17:15.850
Anyway...

01:17:20.479 --> 01:17:21.731
...I'll miss you.

01:17:21.939 --> 01:17:25.276
<i>Don't be sad. Here, take this.</i>

01:17:30.948 --> 01:17:33.159
<i>No, I want you to have it.</i>

01:17:33.409 --> 01:17:35.536
Okay. Thanks.

01:17:37.621 --> 01:17:40.499
<i>Don't worry,
it'll take good care of you.</i>

01:17:46.172 --> 01:17:47.465
We're gonna see Daddy.

01:17:47.757 --> 01:17:50.301
<i>Oh, great.
I was just thinking about James.</i>

01:17:51.010 --> 01:17:54.388
You have to look fantastic.
The blue or the lamb?

01:17:54.555 --> 01:17:56.974
<i>Neither. They both look pretty lame.</i>

01:17:57.683 --> 01:17:58.684
The lamb?

01:17:58.851 --> 01:18:00.728
<i>Not lamb, lame!</i>

01:18:00.936 --> 01:18:04.273
<i>Please don't make me
wear clothes with animals on them.</i>

01:18:05.900 --> 01:18:10.071
<i>I don't like this.
It makes me look stupid.</i>

01:18:11.906 --> 01:18:13.199
You look great.

01:18:13.491 --> 01:18:15.951
<i>I feel like a retard.</i>

01:18:19.747 --> 01:18:23.417
<i>Hey, look at this room!
Look at these guys!</i>

01:18:23.626 --> 01:18:26.796
<i>I bet I can take those apart.
It doesn't look--</i>

01:18:27.046 --> 01:18:29.924
<i>Little metal things.
Where can I stick them?</i>

01:18:30.174 --> 01:18:32.385
<i>Right there in those little holes.</i>

01:18:33.511 --> 01:18:35.179
-Mollie.
<i>-Who's this?</i>

01:18:35.388 --> 01:18:38.766
Hi. This must be Mikey.

01:18:39.266 --> 01:18:42.436
Hi, fella! What you doing?

01:18:42.603 --> 01:18:44.313
What you doing?

01:18:44.522 --> 01:18:45.606
Aren't you--?

01:18:45.815 --> 01:18:48.776
<i>-How about a little milk in your eye?
</i>-Damn it!

01:18:48.984 --> 01:18:50.695
<i>Bull's-eye!</i>

01:18:51.570 --> 01:18:53.656
It's just milk. It won't stain.

01:18:53.864 --> 01:18:56.575
Give me the bottle, Mikey.
That's a good boy.

01:18:58.119 --> 01:19:01.831
He's beautiful, Mollie.
He looks just like you.

01:19:02.039 --> 01:19:04.291
People say that. I don't see it.

01:19:04.500 --> 01:19:08.295
I know the circumstances
you had him under were terrible.

01:19:08.504 --> 01:19:11.757
But when I see him,
I know it wasn't a mistake.

01:19:11.966 --> 01:19:14.301
I bet he's glad to hear that.

01:19:15.386 --> 01:19:19.640
<i>You'll never escape, Skeletor.
Come back here with my grape.</i>

01:19:19.849 --> 01:19:20.850
Don't do that!

01:19:21.058 --> 01:19:22.184
<i>What'd I do?</i>

01:19:26.230 --> 01:19:31.235
People find themselves in situations
they can't always get out of.

01:19:31.485 --> 01:19:33.529
What are you saying?
Mikey, don't touch.

01:19:33.988 --> 01:19:35.698
<i>Well, all right.</i>

01:19:36.866 --> 01:19:40.995
I'm saying I still love you
and I still want you.

01:19:42.204 --> 01:19:43.247
And Mikey?

01:19:44.123 --> 01:19:48.419
You can always count on me
if there's anything you need for him.

01:19:49.837 --> 01:19:51.881
I need a father for him.

01:19:52.340 --> 01:19:53.758
I've gotta be honest.

01:19:54.008 --> 01:19:58.471
I'm living alone for the first time
in 17 years. I'm in therapy.

01:19:58.679 --> 01:20:01.265
I can't be anybody's father now.

01:20:01.515 --> 01:20:05.353
I need to be by myself now.
I've raised my kids.

01:20:06.395 --> 01:20:09.440
Raised them? They're 11 and 9.

01:20:09.648 --> 01:20:11.901
Have they moved out and gotten jobs?

01:20:12.943 --> 01:20:14.570
<i>Too much fruit.</i>

01:20:15.654 --> 01:20:18.324
Well, it wouldn't be fair to Mikey.

01:20:19.533 --> 01:20:20.785
Is he taking a dump?

01:20:20.993 --> 01:20:23.329
No, he's thinking real hard.

01:20:24.580 --> 01:20:25.831
Come on.

01:20:27.375 --> 01:20:29.001
Let's get you cleaned up.

01:20:29.251 --> 01:20:32.546
Why don't you use
the washroom in back, Mollie?

01:20:32.797 --> 01:20:36.050
What will I tell him
when he asks about his daddy?

01:20:36.258 --> 01:20:39.178
<i>No! Not him!
I want James to be the daddy.</i>

01:20:39.387 --> 01:20:42.807
Don't do that here.
That's a $10,000 desk.

01:20:44.642 --> 01:20:45.685
Now it's junk!

01:20:45.893 --> 01:20:49.480
Goddamn it, I'm trying to be honest.
I thought you'd understand.

01:20:49.689 --> 01:20:53.192
Of course I do.
I am a very understanding person.

01:20:53.401 --> 01:20:56.696
I understand you are going
through a selfish phase.

01:20:56.904 --> 01:21:01.826
And I know you'll understand that I am
going through a destructive phase.

01:21:07.039 --> 01:21:09.875
<i>Let's trash the place.
Take that, Tonto.</i>

01:21:16.966 --> 01:21:19.844
I'm sorry I made you wear
that stupid outfit.

01:21:20.344 --> 01:21:23.806
And I'm sorry you had
to meet that mean man.

01:21:24.306 --> 01:21:26.267
You'll never have to see him again.

01:21:26.475 --> 01:21:31.063
Every time I take you someplace,
everybody says how cute you are.

01:21:31.230 --> 01:21:32.231
<i>Naturally.</i>

01:21:32.398 --> 01:21:36.027
The one person who has a genetic bond
treats you like a jerk.

01:21:36.402 --> 01:21:39.822
Let me try it now.
Everybody loves you.

01:21:40.031 --> 01:21:44.410
The kids at the playground.
Ma loves you, Rona loves you...

01:21:44.618 --> 01:21:47.371
...everybody at work loves you.
James loves you.

01:21:48.039 --> 01:21:50.916
Mikey, do you love James?

01:21:53.586 --> 01:21:54.879
<i>Give him a call.</i>

01:21:55.087 --> 01:21:57.381
What, honey?
You want to play telephone?

01:21:57.631 --> 01:21:58.799
<i>Call him.</i>

01:21:59.550 --> 01:22:00.718
Hello?

01:22:02.178 --> 01:22:03.262
It's for you.

01:22:03.471 --> 01:22:07.183
You take this one, I'll take
the other one. Be right back.

01:22:08.267 --> 01:22:09.268
Hello.

01:22:09.477 --> 01:22:12.938
<i>This is Lou Franklin. I got
a problem with your grandfather.</i>

01:22:13.147 --> 01:22:16.942
He's become abusive and violent.
You'll have to pick him up.

01:22:17.151 --> 01:22:18.903
<i>I'll have to call Health and Welfare.</i>

01:22:19.111 --> 01:22:22.198
-No, don't. I'll be right there.
<i>-See you soon.</i>

01:22:33.459 --> 01:22:36.837
-Grandpa, what's going on?
-Look, I'm a hostage.

01:22:37.088 --> 01:22:40.091
He's not a hostage,
he's a mean old bastard.

01:22:40.299 --> 01:22:43.302
Look at my arm.
He gave the nurse a black eye.

01:22:43.511 --> 01:22:45.805
-Don't talk that way.
-They're hiding Dora.

01:22:46.013 --> 01:22:47.932
They're not hiding anyone.

01:22:48.432 --> 01:22:50.601
Then where is she? Where's my wife?

01:22:50.851 --> 01:22:53.938
Sit down. I'll find her for you.

01:22:54.897 --> 01:22:56.857
Let's clean that off your face.

01:22:57.108 --> 01:22:59.944
You want to look good
when you see her, don't you?

01:23:01.696 --> 01:23:04.198
You're my favourite daughter-in-law.

01:23:04.990 --> 01:23:07.618
You're smart and you're a good person.

01:23:08.077 --> 01:23:11.205
That's why Jimmy loves you so much.

01:23:15.459 --> 01:23:16.502
There you go.

01:23:17.420 --> 01:23:20.214
<i>Come on, Ma. Let's go find James.</i>

01:23:20.381 --> 01:23:23.092
You want to see pictures?
I'll show you pictures.

01:23:25.553 --> 01:23:26.804
Grandpa?

01:23:27.513 --> 01:23:30.391
Did you eat
all these candy bars today?

01:23:30.558 --> 01:23:33.310
What candy?
The bastards stole my candy!

01:23:33.561 --> 01:23:35.021
We'll get you some more.

01:23:35.187 --> 01:23:37.231
-Where's the director?
-Down the hall.

01:23:37.440 --> 01:23:39.025
Mikey, come with Mama.

01:23:39.191 --> 01:23:40.735
Later. We're busy.

01:23:40.901 --> 01:23:43.279
-I'll watch him.
-You sure?

01:23:43.487 --> 01:23:45.406
I'll be back in a minute.

01:23:47.408 --> 01:23:51.579
He gets disoriented,
but this isn't his usual behaviour.

01:23:51.746 --> 01:23:54.457
That's why my husband made
arrangements with your orderly.

01:23:55.374 --> 01:23:59.128
It isn't the orderly's responsibility
to control his diet.

01:23:59.336 --> 01:24:02.715
If that's the care he requires,
you need a private nurse.

01:24:02.923 --> 01:24:05.468
That isn't the kind
of care he requires.

01:24:05.718 --> 01:24:07.720
My husband told the orderly...

01:24:07.928 --> 01:24:12.433
...to give him one candy bar a day,
and the orderly agreed.

01:24:12.641 --> 01:24:14.352
He said, "No problem."

01:24:14.560 --> 01:24:18.481
Then that was Bill.
Bill always says "No problem."

01:24:18.773 --> 01:24:19.774
What?

01:24:19.940 --> 01:24:22.234
That's all he can say.
He can't speak English.

01:24:24.403 --> 01:24:26.238
So can Grandpa stay?

01:24:26.697 --> 01:24:27.990
Of course.

01:24:28.324 --> 01:24:29.492
Thank you.

01:24:30.951 --> 01:24:34.038
-Thanks for coming down so fast.
-No problem.

01:24:36.999 --> 01:24:38.542
-Hi.
-Hi.

01:24:41.295 --> 01:24:43.839
I arranged it
so your grandfather can stay.

01:24:44.048 --> 01:24:46.967
I know, I heard.
You didn't have to do that.

01:24:47.218 --> 01:24:49.011
I wanted to do it.

01:24:49.720 --> 01:24:51.931
Let me give you a ride home.

01:24:52.640 --> 01:24:54.850
-Don't bother.
-Fine.

01:24:55.935 --> 01:24:58.813
DJ, time for lunch. Let's go.

01:25:00.064 --> 01:25:01.190
Are you okay with him?

01:25:01.399 --> 01:25:04.443
Get the hell out of here! I'm busy.

01:25:06.320 --> 01:25:07.697
This is Steven.

01:25:07.905 --> 01:25:10.825
This is Paulie.
They're your own little cousins.

01:25:12.451 --> 01:25:14.036
Hi, Vince.

01:25:14.662 --> 01:25:16.622
Hello, Ester.

01:25:24.338 --> 01:25:26.882
I'd like you to meet my grandson.

01:25:27.967 --> 01:25:30.511
<i>There goes James.
James, wait a minute!</i>

01:25:31.595 --> 01:25:36.434
<i>Where's he going? Maybe he's going
downstairs. I'll go and meet him.</i>

01:25:36.934 --> 01:25:38.269
I went to the beauty parlour.

01:25:38.519 --> 01:25:40.229
<i>Where's that elevator?</i>

01:25:41.313 --> 01:25:43.232
<i>Here we go. Going down.</i>

01:25:45.985 --> 01:25:48.029
<i>I'll just press all of these.</i>

01:25:51.365 --> 01:25:55.745
<i>Hey, perfect.
I'll just hitch a ride with the fruit cups.</i>

01:25:57.997 --> 01:25:59.707
<i>Here we go.</i>

01:26:00.458 --> 01:26:01.959
<i>Take her away, boys!</i>

01:26:03.961 --> 01:26:06.589
Mikey?

01:26:06.797 --> 01:26:09.800
-Grandpa, where's Mikey?
-He was just here.

01:26:09.967 --> 01:26:13.387
What do you mean?
How long ago did he leave?

01:26:15.348 --> 01:26:18.476
-I'll check the hallway.
-I'll call the police.

01:26:20.227 --> 01:26:23.314
<i>Which one of you dames
wants to help me find my dad?</i>

01:26:23.564 --> 01:26:25.691
That's Ida's grandson.

01:26:25.900 --> 01:26:29.779
<i>I'm in a hurry. I just saw
the yellow box go by.</i>

01:26:30.446 --> 01:26:33.449
Here, fella.
Go back to your grandma.

01:26:33.657 --> 01:26:35.701
<i>Thanks for nothing, babe.</i>

01:26:35.910 --> 01:26:37.703
Show the police these pictures.

01:26:37.953 --> 01:26:41.374
-I'll check the cafeteria.
-I'll check the hall again.

01:26:41.916 --> 01:26:44.335
<i>I'm on the case now.</i>

01:26:47.254 --> 01:26:51.133
<i>Now that is exactly what I need.</i>

01:26:51.342 --> 01:26:53.969
<i>I'll be able to find him
in one of those.</i>

01:26:54.220 --> 01:26:56.013
<i>Let's see if I remember this.</i>

01:26:56.222 --> 01:26:59.934
<i>I better set this thing down.
Right here. That's a good spot.</i>

01:27:00.142 --> 01:27:01.686
<i>Get that door open.</i>

01:27:02.353 --> 01:27:04.230
<i>What was it James said?</i>

01:27:04.438 --> 01:27:08.109
<i>Let's see.
I just stick this thing right in here.</i>

01:27:08.317 --> 01:27:09.568
<i>There it goes!</i>

01:27:09.777 --> 01:27:12.279
<i>Move the circle around,
and we're off!</i>

01:27:22.540 --> 01:27:25.334
-He's in the back of that car!
-Let's get the cab.

01:27:29.004 --> 01:27:30.089
Stop!

01:27:40.182 --> 01:27:43.227
<i>I got this driving thing knocked.
No problem.</i>

01:27:48.774 --> 01:27:49.984
Move it!

01:27:53.112 --> 01:27:54.864
<i>There he is. Hey, James!</i>

01:27:55.072 --> 01:27:58.159
<i>Look at me. I'm driving!
How about this?</i>

01:28:04.498 --> 01:28:06.000
<i>Where's he going?</i>

01:28:10.087 --> 01:28:11.505
We'll lose them!

01:28:11.672 --> 01:28:12.840
I'll cut them off.

01:28:13.007 --> 01:28:15.468
-You'll lose them!
-We won't lose them!

01:28:17.720 --> 01:28:20.306
<i>I know this alley like
the back of my hand.</i>

01:28:39.909 --> 01:28:41.911
He's gone!

01:28:44.538 --> 01:28:48.459
Mister, you had a little boy
in that car! He's my son!

01:28:48.626 --> 01:28:50.044
I saw him in your car!

01:28:50.628 --> 01:28:53.047
He's about this big.
He's only a year old!

01:28:53.631 --> 01:28:55.675
<i>This is a good place to spot them.</i>

01:28:55.883 --> 01:28:57.510
Mikey!

01:28:58.344 --> 01:28:59.804
Mikey, stop!

01:29:01.806 --> 01:29:03.849
<i>James, is that you?</i>

01:29:04.016 --> 01:29:05.226
Mikey, don't move!

01:29:05.393 --> 01:29:07.144
<i>Hey, James! Mommy!</i>

01:29:09.230 --> 01:29:10.731
<i>Here I come!</i>

01:29:13.776 --> 01:29:15.069
<i>I'm coming, I'm coming.</i>

01:29:25.663 --> 01:29:27.873
<i>Did you see what just happened?</i>

01:29:28.124 --> 01:29:29.625
Give me my baby!

01:29:30.292 --> 01:29:32.211
<i>Ma, did you see that?</i>

01:29:34.380 --> 01:29:36.007
Are you all right, honey?

01:29:36.173 --> 01:29:39.093
Are you all right? Let me see you.

01:29:39.260 --> 01:29:42.722
I can't believe it.
He doesn't have a scratch on him.

01:29:42.888 --> 01:29:45.725
<i>I'm glad I finally
got you both together.</i>

01:29:45.933 --> 01:29:49.770
-I'll take him to the hospital anyway.
-He's a tough kid.

01:29:49.979 --> 01:29:52.064
<i>Ma, I want James to be the daddy.</i>

01:29:54.400 --> 01:29:56.402
-Thanks for your help.
-I'll take you home.

01:30:00.573 --> 01:30:01.574
Dada.

01:30:03.576 --> 01:30:06.704
-He said, "Dada."
-He called you Dada.

01:30:06.912 --> 01:30:09.498
<i>No, I'm talking to hear myself speak.</i>

01:30:09.707 --> 01:30:12.084
-He thinks you're his dad.
-I spent time with him.

01:30:12.293 --> 01:30:14.003
You've spent a lot of time with him.

01:30:15.254 --> 01:30:17.673
He probably thinks
we'll end up together.

01:30:28.309 --> 01:30:31.562
<i>I hope they don't get
stuck together like that.</i>

01:30:36.650 --> 01:30:39.236
<i>Should I tell them
I need a new diaper?</i>

01:30:40.863 --> 01:30:42.740
<i>Nah, I'll wait.</i>

01:31:36.794 --> 01:31:37.795
Hi, honey.

01:31:37.962 --> 01:31:41.048
Mikey, this is your sister, Julie.

01:31:41.215 --> 01:31:44.051
-Say, "Hi, Julie."
-Hi, Julie.

01:31:44.218 --> 01:31:47.388
<i>Don't start with me.
I've had a day you wouldn't believe.</i>

01:31:47.555 --> 01:31:49.557
<i>Can we talk?</i>
